Example of Kas antivirus daemon for Linux. KAV Daemon

1. TCP Daemon, one can specify IP and port, by default localhost:7310 will be used

2. Uses KAV SDK to virus scan specified files.

3. Supports subset of the clamd commands:

   SESSION\n  -- no response,
   PING\n     -- PONG\n,
   SCAN path  -- path: OK\n
              -- ?
   END        -- no response

4. Forks for every new connection.

5. If gets an unknown command just closes TCP session.

6. Uses syslog for logging, DAEMON facility

7. No configuration file, just command line options:

   --version       (-v)
   --help          (-h)
   --ip = X.X.X.X  (-i X.X.X.X)
   --port = number (-p number)
   --no-detach                   do not detach from console, used for debugging

